definition.value: A glycosylarabinose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and D-arabinopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.

A linear amino hexasaccharide comprised of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->3), (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4). It is found in human milk.
The open chain form of L-idose.
